reviewText: I have the book too! WHERE DO WE LIVE?
I've been studying the JFK assassination since 1973. I am a poor reader and I learn better by watching documentaries. I am glad to add it to my collection.

Good video for anyone researching the JFK assassination, Abraham Bolden the first African American Secret Serviceman explains many behind the scenes observations and the climate of hate surrounding the president from the men assigned to protect him.

Awful production. At times Boldens voice is hardly discernible due to totally obsolete sound effects (thunder and rumbling). PQ is worse than could be expected from a DVD-production.
Due to really bad audio-quality the content as such is overall hard to evaluate.
